    • Method Detail

      • extract

        public static Buffer extract​(io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf byteBuf)
        Extracts the underlying Buffer instance that is backing this ByteBuf, if any. This is similar to unwrap() except the return type is a Buffer. If this ByteBuf does not wrap a Buffer, then null is returned.
        Parameters:
        byteBuf - The ByteBuf to extract the Buffer from.
        Returns:
        The Buffer instance that is backing the given ByteBuf, or null if the given ByteBuf is not backed by a Buffer.

      • extractOrCopy

        public static Buffer extractOrCopy​(BufferAllocator allocator,
                                   io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf byteBuf)
        Extracts the underlying Buffer instance that is backing this ByteBuf, if any. This is similar to unwrap() except the return type is a Buffer. If this ByteBuf does not wrap a Buffer, then a new Buffer instance is returned with the contents copied from the given ByteBuf.
        Parameters:
        byteBuf - The ByteBuf to extract the Buffer from.
        Returns:
        The Buffer instance that is backing the given ByteBuf, or a new Buffer containing the contents copied from the given ByteBuf. If the data is copied, the passed ByteBuf will be released.

      • intoByteBuf

        public static io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf intoByteBuf​(Buffer buffer)
        Convert the given Buffer into a ByteBuf using the most optimal method. The contents of both buffers will be mirrored.

        If the given Buffer is a ByteBufBuffer, then its inner ByteBuf is extracted.

        Parameters:
        buffer - The Buffer to convert into a ByteBuf.
        Returns:
        A ByteBuf that uses the given Buffer as a backing store.
